Piecewise Polynomials
A piecewise polynomial function is obtained by dividing the domain of ğ‘‹ into contiguous intervals and representing the function by a separate polynomial in each interval. The rather lengthy Python code chunk below fits some simple piecewise polynomials to simulated data and plots them nicely. Note that most of the code is for plotting.


